        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent-job): surface pending error snapshot when outer timeout fires",
        "body": "### What\n\nFixes `agent.wait` / `sessions_send` timeout diagnostics when a lifecycle `error` is already pending but still inside the 15-second retry grace.\n\n### Why\n\nThe existing retry grace is intentional: embedded runs can emit transient lifecycle `error` events during auth/model failover, and a later lifecycle `start` can cancel the pending error. Before this PR, if the caller's shorter wait deadline fired during that grace window, callers received a generic timeout and lost the useful error reason.\n\n### How\n\nWhen the outer wait deadline fires during a pending lifecycle error, `agent.wait` now returns a non-terminal timeout diagnostic: `status: \"timeout\"`, `error`, and `pendingError: true`. It does not record the pending error as terminal, so a later lifecycle `start` can still recover the run. `sessions_send` returns that timeout reason to the caller while keeping its background A2A follow-up alive, and the SDK treats `pendingError: true` wait payloads as non-terminal accepted runs rather than terminal `timed_out` results.\n\nCloses #52497\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `sessions_send` and SDK/Gateway `agent.wait` callers now receive the pending model/lifecycle error reason on wait timeout without breaking retry-grace recovery semantics.\n\nReal environment tested: Local openclaw/openclaw checkout, Node 24.13.0. Gateway wait, gateway WebSocket `agent.wait`, `sessions_send`, run-wait normalization, and SDK wait normalization exercised with focused tests.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/sdk/src/index.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat.test.ts src/agents/run-wait.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.sessions.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs packages/sdk/src/client.ts packages/sdk/src/index.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent-job.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent-wait-dedupe.ts src/agents/run-wait.ts src/agents/tools/sessions-send-tool.ts src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat.test.ts src/agents/run-wait.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.sessions.test.ts\nenv -u OPENCLAW_TESTBOX pnpm check:changed\n/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-skills/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\nTest Files  7 passed (7)\nTests       246 passed (246)\n\ntouched-file oxlint: exit 0\n\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The pending lifecycle error is exposed as a timeout diagnostic with `pendingError: true`; the pending error is not cached as terminal; a later lifecycle `start` + `end` still resolves as `ok`; `sessions_send` returns the pending error reason and keeps the background follow-up path alive; SDK `Run.wait()` keeps pending-error wait deadlines non-terminal.\n\nWhat was not tested: Production load with a real provider 429; concurrent multi-job races beyond the covered single-run regression; full CI completion after the maintainer fixup. Local `check:changed` typechecks passed, but its broad lint phase is currently blocked by an unrelated existing oxlint finding in `src/channels/message/inbound-reply-dispatch.ts:279`.\n",
        "branch": "fix/agent-job-pending-error-snapshot",
